If you haven't configured AbuseHelper earlier, run the following commands: 
## Copy & Paste below
cp -r /usr/local/share/examples/abusehelper /etc/                                                                     
chown -R root:_abusehe /etc/abusehelper/ 
chmod 750 /etc/abusehelper/

mkdir /var/log/abusehelper
chown _abusehe:_abusehe /var/log/abusehelper
chmod 770 /var/log/abusehelper
## End Copy & Paste

And then edit the following files:

 * /etc/abusehelper/config.ini
 * /etc/abusehelper/customers.ini
 * /etc/abusehelper/templates/*
